RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 51. Claiming Purse 7150. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TUATHA vied for the early lead from the inside and drew off to be well clear under steady pressure. CAROLS KITTEN was coaxed along two deep and was no match for the winner in the drive to finish second best. GODDESS OF WONDER was hustled from the gate, raced near the rail throughout and kept on to the wire. MISS RITA dropped near the back of the pack early on, advanced four to five wide around the far turn and improved position while racing from the outside. SHE'S A PLAYER was off a step slow, raced three to four wide into the upper stretch and never threatened. BOUJEE BRITT chased the pace four deep from the outside foes and weakened. RUNNIN BOOTS chased from the outside, checked early on and faded in the drive.
